---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import CodeBlock from "../../components/CodeBlock.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Language Reference" currentPath="/docs/language">
  <h1>Language Reference</h1>
  <p style="color:var(--c-text-secondary);font-size:var(--fs-md);margin-bottom:var(--s-6);">
    A complete reference of Visuall syntax, types, and semantics.
  </p>

  <h2>Comments</h2>
  <CodeBlock code={`## Single-line comment
### Multi-line
    comment ###`} />

  <h2>Variables &amp; Types</h2>
  <p>Visuall is statically typed with type inference. Basic types: <code>int</code>, <code>float</code>, <code>str</code>, <code>bool</code>, <code>null</code>.</p>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`name = "Visuall"
age = 25
pi = 3.14159
active = true
nothing = null`}
  />

  <h2>Functions &amp; Lambdas</h2>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`define add(a: int, b: int) -> int:
    return a + b

## Lambdas
square = x -> x ** 2
transform = (x, y) -> x + y

## Closures
define make_adder(n: int):
    return x -> x + n`}
  />

  <h2>Classes</h2>
  <p>Single inheritance with <code>extends</code>. Constructor is <code>init</code>. Use <code>this</code> for field access.</p>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`class Point:
    init(x: int, y: int):
        this.x = x
        this.y = y

    define magnitude() -> float:
        return sqrt(this.x ** 2 + this.y ** 2)

class Point3D extends Point:
    init(x: int, y: int, z: int):
        super.init(x, y)
        this.z = z

p = Point3D(3, 4, 12)
print(p.magnitude())`}
  />

  <h2>Control Flow</h2>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`## If / elsif / else
if 18 <= age <= 65:
    status = "working age"
elsif age > 65:
    status = "retired"
else:
    status = "young"

## For-in loops
for item in [1, 2, 3]:
    print(item)

for i in range(0, 10, 2):
    print(i)

## While loops
while running:
    if done:
        break
    continue

## Context managers (with)
with open("file.txt") as f:
    data = f.read()`}
  />

  <h2>Data Structures</h2>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`## Lists
numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
numbers[0] = 99

## Tuples
coords = (10, 20, 30)
x, y, z = coords           ## unpacking

## Dictionaries
config = {"name": "app", "version": 1}

## List comprehensions
squares = [x * x for x in range(10)]
evens = [x for x in numbers if x % 2 == 0]

## Slicing
first_three = numbers[0:3]
every_other = numbers[0:5:2]
tail = numbers[1:]`}
  />

  <h2>Strings &amp; F-strings</h2>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`greeting = "Hello, World!"
message = f"Result: {value}, took {ms}ms"
multipart = f"{name} scored {score} / {total}"`}
  />

  <h2>Error Handling</h2>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`try:
    risky()
catch IOError as e:
    print(f"IO error: {e}")
catch Error as e:
    print(f"Error: {e}")
finally:
    cleanup()`}
  />

  <h2>Match Statements</h2>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`## Basic matching
match status:
    case 200:
        print("OK")
    case 404:
        print("Not Found")
    case _:
        print("other")

## Guards
match value:
    case x if x > 0:
        print("positive")
    case x if x < 0:
        print("negative")
    case _:
        print("zero")

## String and bool patterns
match name:
    case "alice":
        role = "admin"
    case _:
        role = "user"`}
  />

  <h2>Generators (yield)</h2>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`define evens(n: int) -> int:
    i = 0
    while i < n:
        yield i
        i = i + 2

for v in evens(10):
    print(v)`}
  />
  <p style="font-size:var(--fs-sm);color:var(--c-text-secondary);">
    A <code>yield</code> inside a function turns it into a generator: the function collects all yielded values into a list that is returned.
  </p>

  <h2>Enums</h2>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`enum Color:
    RED
    GREEN
    BLUE

x = Color.RED`}
  />

  <h2>Decorators</h2>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`@cache
@log
define compute(x: int) -> int:
    return x * 2`}
  />

  <h2>Generics &amp; Nullable Types</h2>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`## Generic type parameters
define clamp<T: int>(x: T, lo: T, hi: T) -> T:
    ...

## Nullable return type
define find(items: list, key: str) -> str?:
    ## returns str or null
    ...`}
  />

  <h2>Walrus Operator</h2>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`if (n := len(data)) > 10:
    print(f"too large: {n}")`}
  />

  <h2>isinstance</h2>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`if isinstance(obj, Animal):
    obj.speak()`}
  />

  <h2>Operators</h2>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`## Arithmetic
x = 2 ** 10        ## exponentiation
y = 17 // 3        ## integer division
z = 17 % 3         ## modulo

## Bitwise
a = x & 0xFF
b = x | mask
c = x ^ toggle
d = x << 4
e = x >> 2

## Logical
flag = true and not false
result = a or b

## Chained comparisons
if 0 <= x <= 100:
    print("in range")`}
  />

  <h2>Module System</h2>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`## Import a whole module
import math
print(math.sqrt(16))

## Import specific names
from string import upper, split
print(upper("hello"))

## Multi-file compilation
## visuallc resolves imports via vsl.lock automatically`}
  />

  <h2>Debug Flags</h2>
  <p>Compiler diagnostics available via CLI flags:</p>
  <CodeBlock
    code={`./visuallc --tokens file.vsl       # Dump token stream
./visuallc --ast file.vsl          # Dump parsed AST
./visuallc --emit-ir file.vsl      # Emit LLVM IR to stdout
./visuallc --dump-modules file.vsl # Print resolved module paths
./visuallc --gc-stats file.vsl -o p# Print GC statistics at exit`}
    lang="bash"
  />
</DocsLayout>
